# Curated list of Debian SOURCE packages to build into packages-out/.
# One source-package name per line. Blank lines and #-comments are ignored.
#
# Build the whole list with:   scripts/build-all.sh
# (which just feeds these names to build-pkg.sh in a single container run).
#
# Scope reminder (see CLAUDE.md): this is an on-demand, accumulating set you
# curate — NOT a full Debian mirror. Keep it to packages you actually want on
# the router. Each entry also pulls its build-deps as prebuilt .debs; a few
# names here can still mean a lot of disk, so add deliberately.
#
# Tip: building is fault-tolerant — an entry that fails to build is reported and
# skipped, and the rest of the list still builds and indexes.
lsof
forkstat
fping
hping3
sysstat
tcpdump
mtr-tiny
iperf3
ethtool
# socat
ngrep
traceroute
tmux
htop
screen
